2)I don't know quite how you propose that fusion plants all would be used to produce weapons-grade materials.  Extra neutrons from the reaction I can buy, but these are mainly lost neutrons.  There would actually be far greater loss of neutrons in commercial fission reactors than fusion reactors.  Proliferators could use fission plants more easily than fusion plants, in terms of finding neutron sources for fissile materials.  This is due to the fact that it's a chain reaction producing the fissile materials.  Neutron absorption isn't (primarily) just a random occurance for Pu-238.<br>
